	<abstract>
		<para>This article is intended to give a hands-on introduction to using the KGI Build and Configuration 
		Toolkit (KGI Toolkit).</para>
	</abstract>
	<section><title>A few words before you start</title>
		<para>
		This document is intended to help you getting familiar with the build system used with KGI.
		This document will sometimes make references to shell scripts or Makefiles included with the
		KGI Toolkit source distribution.
		Please be aware that if information given in this document and scripts or Makefiles referenced
		are contradictionary, this document should be considered to be out of date.
		That is, the actual Toolkit implementation takes precedence over information presented
		in this document.
		However, if you spot a section where this is the case, please notify the author of this document about
		this condition so he can resolve this problem.
		</para>
	</section>
